Player Management

Add Player - Creates a new player (auto-numbered: Player 1, Player 2, etc.)

Dealing Cards

Deal <card> to Player <#>/Dealer - Deal a specific card face-up

Example: Deal A to Player 1, Deal K to Dealer


Deal Face Down to Player <#>/Dealer - Deal a card without specifying value

Example: Deal Face Down to Dealer



Revealing Face Down Cards

Flip Player <#>/Dealer <card> - Reveal a face down card with its value

Example: Flip Dealer K, Flip Player 1 A



Drawing Cards (Hitting)

Player <#> Hit <card> - Player draws a specific card

Example: Player 1 Hit 5, Player 2 Hit Q


Dealer Hit <card> - Dealer draws a specific card

Example: Dealer Hit 7



Probability Analysis

Probability of <number> after Player <#>/Dealer hit - Calculate odds of hand total after next card

Example: Probability of 21 after Player 1 hit
Shows % chance of being greater than, less than, or equal to the target



Game Management

Status (or State, Show) - Display all card locations and counts
Clear Hands (or Clear Hand, Clear) - Move all hands to discard pile (keeps players)
Shuffle (or Reset, New Deck) - Reset to fresh 52-card deck, remove all players

Card Tracking Zones:

Deck - Undealt cards
Face Down - Cards dealt but not yet revealed
Player Hands - Each player's visible cards
Dealer Hand - Dealer's visible cards
Discard Pile - Used cards from previous hands

The agent tracks all 52 cards across all zones throughout the session!
